<link href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=84&amp;p=357#p357"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[New &lt;location&gt; element]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=84&amp;p=357#p357"><![CDATA[
I noticed the &lt;time&gt; element in HTML 5. Excellent idea!<br /><br />What about adding a &lt;location&gt; element, to indicate geographical location?<br /><br />There would be optional latitude, longitude, altitude, head, tilt and range attributes (following <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GeoTagging" class="postlink">GeoBloggers</a>conventions), in addition to text content.<br /><br />For example,<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;p&gt;We are meeting at &lt;location&gt;Canary Wharf&lt;/location&gt;, &lt;time&gt;8 Aug, 5pm&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/p&gt;.</code></dd></dl><br /><br />or <br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;location&gt;Canary Wharf &lt;img src=&quot;canarywharf.jpg&quot;/&gt;&lt;/location&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />or<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;p&gt;Please send mail to &lt;location&gt;99 Canada Square, Canary Wharf, London, E14 0XX&lt;/location&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />It's basically a properly semantic version of geo-tagged microformats, and has similar uses - for example, it could enable pop-up online maps if you click on them. If both a location and a time are present, it could integrate with your calendar.<br /><br />In addition, it would be great to enable &lt;location&gt; in forms, so the user has help (e.g. a map) to pick the appropriate place before submitting the form.<br /><br />And it may help resolve some of the uncertainties surrounding &lt;address&gt;...<br /><br />What do you think?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=135">chris.f.jay@gmail.com</a> — Mon Jul 09, 2007 1:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
